name: IDataType Interface
description: The IDataType interface is the root interface for converting all the Tekla.Structures.Datatype.* types to basic types supported by the Tekla Structures Object Dialog tree.
summary:
The IDataType interface is the root interface for converting all the
            Tekla.Structures.Datatype.* types to basic types supported by the
            Tekla Structures Object Dialog tree.

name: IDoubleDataType Interface
description: The IDoubleDataType interface is an interface for the Tekla.Structures.Datatype.* types whose value is a double.
summary:
The IDoubleDataType interface is an interface for the Tekla.Structures.Datatype.*
            types whose value is a double.

name: IIntDataType Interface
description: The IIntDataType interface is an interface for the Tekla.Structures.Datatype.* types whose value is an integer.
summary:
The IIntDataType interface is an interface for the Tekla.Structures.Datatype.*
            types whose value is an integer.

name: IStringDataType Interface
description: The IStringDataType interface is an interface for the Tekla.Structures.Datatype.* types whose value is a string.
summary:
The IStringDataType interface is an interface for the Tekla.Structures.Datatype.*
            types whose value is a string.

name: IAxisAlignedBoundingBox Interface
description: The IAxisAlignedBoundingBox interface is implemented by objects that have an axis aligned bounding box.
summary: The IAxisAlignedBoundingBox interface is implemented by objects that have an axis aligned bounding box.

name: IEvents Interface
description: Interface for the Events class allows the user to register event listeners for Drawings events. This interface allows the Marshaling of the Events class with Trimble.Remoting
summary:
Interface for the Events class allows the user to register event listeners for Drawings events.
            This interface allows the Marshaling of the Events class with Trimble.Remoting

name: IHasChildren Interface
description: The IHasChildren interface is implemented by objects that have child objects.
summary: The IHasChildren interface is implemented by objects that have child objects.

name: IHideable Interface
description: The IHideable interface is used for each object that can be hidden in the drawing.
summary: The IHideable interface is used for each object that can be hidden in the drawing.

name: IIsEqual Interface
description: The IIsEqual interface is for comparing objects using the function IsEqual().
summary: The IIsEqual interface is for comparing objects using the function IsEqual().

name: IMovableRelative Interface
description: The IMovableRelative interface is implemented by objects that can be moved.
summary: The IMovableRelative interface is implemented by objects that can be moved.

name: IObjectAlignedBoundingBox Interface
description: The IObjectAlignedBoundingBox interface is implemented by objects that have an object aligned bounding box.
summary: The IObjectAlignedBoundingBox interface is implemented by objects that have an object aligned bounding box.

name: IPlacing Interface
description: The IPlacing interface is for objects that can have different placings.
summary: The IPlacing interface is for objects that can have different placings.

name: IPreferredPlacing Interface
description: The IPreferredPlacing interface is for objects that can have different preferred placing types.
summary: The IPreferredPlacing interface is for objects that can have different preferred placing types.

name: IRelatedObjects Interface
description: The IRelatedObjects interface is implemented by objects that have related objects.
summary: The IRelatedObjects interface is implemented by objects that have related objects.

name: IResizeable Interface
description: The IResizeable interface is implemented by objects that can be resized.
summary: The IResizeable interface is implemented by objects that can be resized.

name: IUIEvents Interface
description: Interface for the Events class allows the user to register event listeners for DrawingUI events. This interface allows the Marshaling of the Events class with Trimble.Remoting
summary:
Interface for the Events class allows the user to register event listeners for DrawingUI events.
            This interface allows the Marshaling of the Events class with Trimble.Remoting

name: IBoundingVolume Interface
description: The BoundingVolume interface represents any generic 3D bounding volume.
summary: The BoundingVolume interface represents any generic 3D bounding volume.

name: ICurve Interface
description: Interface that represents an abstract curved geometry defined by a set of points. This interface is intended to be the base class of 3D curves.
summary:
Interface that represents an abstract curved geometry defined by a set of points. This interface is intended
            to be the base class of 3D curves.

name: IAssemblable Interface
description: The IAssemblable interface dictates which model objects are capabable of belonging to an assembly at the leaf level.
summary: The IAssemblable interface dictates which model objects are capabable of belonging to an assembly at the leaf level.

name: IEvents Interface
description: Interface for the Events class allows the user to register event listeners for Model events. This interface allows the Marshaling of the Events class with Trimble.Remoting
summary:
Interface for the Events class allows the user to register event listeners for Model events.
            This interface allows the Marshaling of the Events class with Trimble.Remoting

name: IGeometryNode Interface
description: The IGeometryNode interface represents geometry tree node. This is implemented by concrete classes for the various types of geometry nodes
summary: The IGeometryNode interface represents geometry tree node. This is implemented by concrete classes for the various types of geometry nodes

name: IGeometryNodeVisitor Interface
description: The IGeometryNodeVisitor interface is implemented by classes visiting geometry nodes
summary: The IGeometryNodeVisitor interface is implemented by classes visiting geometry nodes

name: ISolid Interface
description: The ISolid interface represents a physical object in the model or a drawing created by a part instance. The solid instance can be used to query the actual geometry of the part.
summary:
The ISolid interface represents a physical object in the model or a drawing created by a part instance.
            The solid instance can be used to query the actual geometry of the part.
